Fix stream SAC coordinator not re-notifying a deactivating consumer that is
re-selected as active.

When a consumer's stepping-down consumer_update response triggers the
coordinator's command_activate_consumer handler, the previously-active
consumer (still in {CONNECTED, DEACTIVATING}) is treated as the "current
active" (ActCsr) because is_active({_, DEACTIVATING}) -> true. The handler
then sets all connected consumers to {CONNECTED, WAITING} and calls
evaluate_active_consumer/1, which picks a new active by
PartitionIndex rem length(Consumers). When that pick happens to be the same
consumer that just stepped down (?SAME_CSR(Csr, ActCsr) = true), the
existing "same active consumer as before, no need to notify it" branch
suppresses the sac notification -- leaving the coordinator believing the
consumer is active while its client has already been told active=false.
The group is silently stranded and never delivers.

The condition is deterministic given the topology: with N partitions and
K consumers joining simultaneously, partitions whose PartitionIndex mod K
selects the first consumer -- and which subscribe after another consumer
has already caused a rebalance -- are stranded.

Only skip the sac notification when the previous active was truly
{CONNECTED, ACTIVE}. If it was DEACTIVATING, its client has just been
notified to step down and must be re-notified when it is re-selected.

--- a/deps/rabbit/src/rabbit_stream_sac_coordinator.erl
+++ b/deps/rabbit/src/rabbit_stream_sac_coordinator.erl
@@ -386,12 +386,16 @@
                         %% do we need effects or not?
                         Effects =
                             case Csr of
-                                Csr when ?SAME_CSR(Csr, ActCsr) ->
+                                Csr when ?SAME_CSR(Csr, ActCsr) andalso
+                                         ActCsr#consumer.status =:= ?CONN_ACT ->
                                     %% it is the same active consumer as before
                                     %% no need to notify it
                                     [];
                                 _ ->
                                     %% new active consumer, need to notify it
+                                    %% (also fires when the previous "active" was
+                                    %% deactivating -- its client has been told to
+                                    %% step down and must be re-notified)
                                     [notify_csr_effect(Csr, S, Name, true)]
                             end,
                         {G2, Effects}
